commitResults.messageTitle: implemented skeletal version, changed duke to HEAD and changed logo
completed level 1, echoes input and exits when input GET SCHWIFTY
Level 2 completed, added an arraylist to keep track of inputs and prints the list when list is entered
added class to represent Task and completed level 3
created todo, event and deadline classes. yet to integrate to the functionality of Duke
added functionality for level 4, works as expected from manual testing
implemented the deletion of tasks, and added a new error to handle selecting an index out of range for delete, mark and unmark operations. Not yet integrated
added archive class to manage tasks. added abstraction to reduce the amount of code in Duke.java.
Allow the saving and retrieval of tasks between uses of the chatbot
commitResults.messageBody:
Users are not able to save tasks between separate uses of the chatbot.

using filereaders and writers we can save the tasks in a text file.

This gives a simple implementation of a local database

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to understand date times given in dd/MM/yyyy HH:mm format and prompt for the correct format otherwise
commitResults.messageBody:
Date was previously treated as a string, which creates problems when trying to do chronological operations on tasks.

Implemented using java LocalDateTime, receives in one format and prints in another
